      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__arch-threads_1ga05c03d97386bc973a403102f4c048444" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int arch_swap</definition>
        <argsstring>(unsigned int key)</argsstring>
        <name>arch_swap</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="lib_2libc_2minimal_2include_2sys_2types_8h_1a4089fb16419d359081465355db05f846" kindref="member">unsigned</ref> int</type>
          <declname>key</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Cooperatively context switch. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Must be called with interrupts locked with the provided key. This is the older-style context switching method, which is incompatible with SMP. New arch ports, either SMP or UP, are encouraged to implement <ref refid="group__arch-threads_1gab411d82ce5b60f062171f5a19e33e025" kindref="member">arch_switch()</ref> instead.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>key</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Interrupt locking key </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>If woken from blocking on some kernel object, the result of that blocking operation. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
